import plotly.graph_objects as go fig = go.Figure() fig.add_trace(go.Histogram( x=df["price"], nbinsx=30, marker_color="#ff6b6b", opacity=0.7, hovertemplate="Price: $%{x:,.0f}
Count: %{y}" )) fig.update_layout( title={"text": "Housing Price Distribution", "x": 0.5, "xanchor": "center"}, xaxis_title="Price ($)", yaxis_title="Frequency", template="plotly_white", height=400, showlegend=False, xaxis=dict(tickformat="$,.0f") )
charts.title: Housing Price Distribution

charts.chart_spec:
import plotly.graph_objects as go bedroom_avg = df.groupby("bedrooms")["price"].mean().sort_index() fig = go.Figure() fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=bedroom_avg.index, y=bedroom_avg.values, marker_color="#45b7d1", text=[f"${val:,.0f}" for val in bedroom_avg.values], textposition="auto", hovertemplate="Bedrooms: %{x}
Average Price: $%{y:,.0f}" )) fig.update_layout( title={"text": "Average Price by Bedrooms", "x": 0.5, "xanchor": "center"}, xaxis_title="Number of Bedrooms", yaxis_title="Average Price ($)", template="plotly_white", height=400, showlegend=False, yaxis=dict(tickformat="$,.0f") )
charts.title: Average Price by Bedrooms

charts.chart_spec: import plotly.graph_objects as go fig = go.Figure() conditions = sorted(df["condition"].unique()) colors_list = ["#ff6b6b", "#4ecdc4", "#45b7d1", "#96ceb4", "#ffeaa7"] for i, condition in enumerate(conditions): condition_data = df[df["condition"] == condition]["price"] fig.add_trace(go.Box( y=condition_data, name=f"Condition {condition}", marker_color=colors_list[i % len(colors_list)], boxmean="sd" )) fig.update_layout( title={"text": "Price Distribution by Condition", "x": 0.5, "xanchor": "center"}, xaxis_title="Condition", yaxis_title="Price ($)", template="plotly_white", height=400, showlegend=False, yaxis=dict(tickformat="$,.0f") )
charts.title: Price Distribution by Condition

charts.chart_spec: import plotly.graph_objects as go fig = go.Figure() fig.add_trace(go.Scattermapbox( lat=df["lat"], lon=df["long"], mode="markers", marker=dict( size=10, color=df["price"], colorscale="Viridis", showscale=True, colorbar=dict(title="Price ($)"), opacity=0.7 ), text=[f"Price: ${p:,.0f}" for p in df["price"]], hovertemplate="%{text}" )) fig.update_layout( title={"text": "Housing Prices by Location", "x": 0.5, "xanchor": "center"}, mapbox=dict( style="open-street-map", center=dict(lat=df["lat"].mean(), lon=df["long"].mean()), zoom=10 ), height=500, margin=dict(l=0, r=0, t=40, b=0) )
charts.title: Housing Prices by Location
